2.1 ABC Classification Analysis

2.1.1 What is ABC Analysis?

ABC Analysis Definition

ABC Analysis is a powerful inventory management technique based on the Pareto Principle (80/20 rule). It categorizes items into three classes based on their consumption value or volume:

  • Class A (High Priority): Items that represent approximately 80% of total consumption volume but only 20% of total items. These are your most critical products requiring maximum attention, tight inventory control, and frequent monitoring.
  • Class B (Medium Priority): Items representing approximately 15% of consumption volume and 30% of items. These require moderate control with periodic reviews and standard ordering procedures.
  • Class C (Low Priority): Items representing only 5% of consumption volume but 50% of total items. These can be managed with simple controls, bulk ordering, or just-in-time delivery.

Why ABC Analysis Matters for Your Medical Distribution Business:

  • Focus Resources: Concentrate your efforts on high-impact items (Class A)
  • Optimize Cash Flow: Invest inventory dollars where they matter most
  • Maximize ROI: Higher service levels on items that drive revenue
  • Efficient Operations: Different management strategies for different item classes

ABC Analysis Key Findings

Perfect Pareto Distribution Confirmed:
  • Class A Items: Only 206 items (10.1% of inventory) drive 79.9% of total consumption
  • Top Opportunity: EXAMINATION GLOVES alone represents 81,393 units (9.44% of total volume)
  • Strategic Focus: Managing just the top 20 A-class items effectively controls 80% of your business volume
Business Strategy Implications:
  • Immediate Action: Secure reliable supply chains for all Class A items
  • Inventory Investment: Allocate 80% of inventory budget to Class A items
  • Competitive Advantage: Offer superior service levels on high-volume items
  • Quick Wins: Focus sales efforts on Class A items for fastest revenue growth
Operational Recommendations:
  • Class A: Daily monitoring, safety stock, multiple suppliers, premium service
  • Class B: Weekly reviews, standard inventory policies, regular supplier relationships
  • Class C: Monthly/quarterly reviews, bulk ordering, consider dropshipping
